  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed double storey side extension, by reason of its scale, siting and design would represent an unsympathetic and uncharacteristic addition to the dwelling house. The scale and massing of the proposed extension would not be subservient or proportionate in its design when viewed against the scale and context of the existing property. Furthermore, the scale of the proposal will lead to a loss of openness which is characteristic of corner plots within the area. The proposal is thereby detrimental to the character and appearance of the street scene, dwelling house and the distinctive Becontree Estate. The proposal is therefore contrary to:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;- National Planning Policy Framework (MHCLG, February 2019);&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;- Policies 7.1, 7.4 and 7.6 of The London Plan (March 2016);&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;- Policy D4 and D8 of the Draft London Plan Intended to Publish (December 2019);&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;- Policies CP2 and CP3 of the LDF Core Strategy (July 2010);&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;- Policies BP2, and BP11 of the LDF Borough Wide Development Plan Policies DPD (March 2011);&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;- The Residential Extensions and Alterations Supplementary Planning Document (February 2012);&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;- Policies SP2, DMD1, DMD4 and SPP6 of the Draft Local Plan (Regulation 19 Consultation version, October 2020&lt;/p&gt;"
